# 🗄️ File Storage Service

A fully automated **File Storage API system** powered by Docker Compose.

---

# 🚀 Quick Start

## 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone <repository-url>
cd file-storage-service

Start with Docker Compose
docker-compose up -d

System is Ready ✅

Backend API:
http://localhost:8080

MinIO Console:
http://localhost:9001

Username: minioadmin
Password: minioadmin123

🔑 API Key Management
1. Generate a New API Key

The first API key can be generated without authentication:

curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/keys/generate \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"name": "My First Key"}'

Response
{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "My First Key",
  "apiKey": "YOUR_API_KEY_HERE",
  "maskedKey": "ABCD****WXYZ",
  "createdAt": "2026-03-03T...",
  "isActive": true
}

⚠️ Important: The apiKey is shown only once. Make sure to save it securely.


📡 API Endpoints
🔐 All endpoints require the X-API-Key header
Upload File
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/files/upload \
  -H "X-API-Key: YOUR_API_KEY" \
  -F "file=@/path/to/file.pdf"

Download File
curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/api/files/{fileId} \
  -H "X-API-Key: YOUR_API_KEY" \
  -O

Get File Metadata
curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/api/files/metadata/{fileId} \
  -H "X-API-Key: YOUR_API_KEY"


List All Files
curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/api/files/list \
  -H "X-API-Key: YOUR_API_KEY"


Delete File
curl -X DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/files/{fileId} \
  -H "X-API-Key: YOUR_API_KEY"

List API Keys
curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/api/keys/list \
  -H "X-API-Key: YOUR_API_KEY"

Delete API Key
curl -X DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/keys/{id} \
  -H "X-API-Key: YOUR_API_KEY"

🏗️ Architecture

┌─────────────┐      ┌──────────────┐      ┌──────────┐
│   Client    │─────▶│  Spring Boot │─────▶│  MinIO   │
└─────────────┘      │     API      │      │ Storage  │
                     └──────────────┘      └──────────┘
                            │
                            ▼
                     ┌──────────────┐
                     │  PostgreSQL  │
                     │   Metadata   │
                     └──────────────┘

┘
🗄️ Database Schema
api_keys

id

key_hash

name

created_at

last_used_at

is_active

file_metadata

id

file_id

original_name

stored_name

file_size

content_type

bucket_name

object_name

uploaded_by_key_id

uploaded_at

download_count

🛠️ Tech Stack

Java 17

Spring Boot 3.2

PostgreSQL (metadata storage)

MinIO (object storage)

Docker & Docker Compose

BCrypt (API key hashing)

🔒 Security

✅ API Key authentication
✅ BCrypt hashing for keys
✅ One-time key display
✅ Rate limiting (future improvement)
✅ Audit logging

📊 MinIO Console

Access the MinIO web interface:

URL:
http://localhost:9001

Credentials:

Username: minioadmin
Password: minioadmin123

🧪 Testing

You can test the API using:

Postman

cURL

Import your endpoints into Postman and start testing.

📝 Notes

Maximum file size: 100MB

API keys are hashed using BCrypt

Files are stored in MinIO

File metadata is stored in PostgreSQL


